Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Fyshwick is the most popular of the three industrial suburbs of Canberra evolving from a standard industrial precinct into a more modern industrial area including bulky goods sales, wholesale and standard industrial uses.

Geelong Street is a wide road running directly off Canberra Avenue so is therefore great for truck access. No. 24 is located approx half way down the Street on the right hand side.

24 Geelong Street is a regular shaped block comprising a brick built double bay clear span warehouse constructed in the 1980s. The warehouse is of steel frame with pitched roof and is accessed via two large roller doors to the front making it easy to reverse trucks into. The windows are fitted with steel security bars and can also include drawing boards and pallet racking if required.

The building contains two internal offices / showroom / reception area to the front which have separate swing door access for customers. This area has tiled floors, a wall mounted air conditioner, ceiling fans and down lighting.

The rear of the warehouse leads onto an enclosed and secure yard area which is accessed via another roller door.

APPROXIMATE AREAS:
Warehouse 624sqm
Office / Reception 85sqm
Rear Secure Yard 296sqm
Block Area:  1,219sqm

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Functional Warehouse with Office, Reception & Yard!

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Easy access to Canberra Ave & Monaro Hwy

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in the busy industrial/ bulky goods retailing area of Fyshwick, 23 Yallourn Street offers a regular shaped block of land measuring approximately 2,855sqm. The block is relatively flat with 38m* frontage to Yallourn Street and 77m* depth.

Key features:

• 2,855sqm* flat block
• Zoned IZ2 (Industrial Mixed Use)
• 38m* frontage to Yallourn Street
• Easy access to Canberra Ave & Monaro Highway
• Ideal for retail, office or industrial uses
• Generous off-street parking
• Surrounded by established retail brands

The property is offered for sale by Public Auction Date TBC.

Please contact Mark Nicholls or Amit Paradkar from CBRE for further information.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: RARE OPPORTUNITY TO PURCHASE A MEDIUM SIZE BLOCK IN FYSHWICK

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
.. here is your opportunity to purchase a warehouse with office and storage yard in Canberra's tightly held suburb, Fyshwick!

32 Geelong Street is a rectangular shaped site measuring approx 2,845sqm with easy access to Canberra Avenue. Improvements comprise an industrial warehouse with office. The site also has a large rear yard which is accessed via a roller door at the rear or driveway at the side of the building.

The property can be sold on a sale and leaseback basis to the owner / occupier, G&H Aluminium Fabricators or with vacant possession to an owner occupier or developer.

G&H do not require the yard area at the rear, so a proposed leaseback will be on the improvements only, providing an opportunity for the purchaser to occupy, lease or develop the yard separately with income from the building.

Please contact CB Richard Ellis for further information.
